&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div itemprop="articleBody" class="msgBody"&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;*Contact emails*
&lt;a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection" class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="97f8b9b9b9d7f0f8f8f0fbf2b9f4f8fa"&gt;[email&#160;protected]&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection" class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="59212c777777193e36363e353c773a3634"&gt;[email&#160;protected]&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;pre&gt;

*Specification*&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://wicg.github.io/serial/"&gt;https://wicg.github.io/serial/&lt;/a&gt;

*Design Docs*
&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://web.dev/serial/"&gt;https://web.dev/serial/&lt;/a&gt;


*Chrome Status Entry*&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://chromestatus.com/feature/6043992171085824"&gt;https://chromestatus.com/feature/6043992171085824&lt;/a&gt;

*Platforms*
Android

*Summary*
Web Serial API becomes fully supported on Android.

Web Serial API is supported on desktop platforms
&lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://groups.google.com/a/chromium.org/g/blink-dev/c/RCtZPCQLLOQ/m/R-vroA4CBQAJ"&gt;https://groups.google.com/a/chromium.org/g/blink-dev/c/RCtZPCQLLOQ/m/R-vroA4CBQAJ&lt;/a&gt;&gt;,
no behavioral changes are expected here.

Web Serial API is partially supported on Android for Bluetooth RFCOMM
&lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://groups.google.com/a/chromium.org/g/blink-dev/c/BqUGCcurReE/m/XbuAYkRxEQAJ"&gt;https://groups.google.com/a/chromium.org/g/blink-dev/c/BqUGCcurReE/m/XbuAYkRxEQAJ&lt;/a&gt;&gt;
.

Web Serial API for non-BT serial ports becomes supported by using Android
Serial API, which will become available in 2026Q2 on a limited set of
devices. For other devices no behavioral changes are expected.

*Blink components*
Blink &gt; Serial

*Estimated milestone*
M149

*Tracking Bug*
crbug.com/365514951

